{
  "user_intent_preservation": {
    "original_goal": "Implement 3-phase PWM motor control on KIT_A3G_TC4D7_LITE (TC4Dx) using eGTM0 ATOM2 with CDTM complementary outputs routed to P20.8/9, P20.10/11, P20.12/13, driven by a unified PWM driver.",
    "functional_behavior": "Generate 20 kHz center-aligned, complementary PWM for phases U, V, W with 1 µs deadtime via CDTM; synchronize start and updates across phases; allow per-phase independent duty updates; and trigger a single period-event ISR on CPU0 with priority 20.",
    "technical_approach": "Use the unified IfxEgtm_Pwm driver on EGTM0 ATOM2 channels 0(U),1(V),2(W) with CDTM; set clocks (ATOM=FXCLK0, DTM=CLK0) via IfxEgtm_Cmu and IfxEgtm_Dtm; map TOUTSEL pins via IfxEgtm_PinMap_setAtomTout to Port 20; configure center-aligned mode and deadtime through IfxEgtm_Pwm init; start channels synchronously and update duties at runtime with IfxEgtm_Pwm_update* APIs; install a period-event ISR on CPU0 and call IfxEgtm_Pwm_interruptHandler from the ISR."
  },
